IN THE 40'S, MOST NY PUBLIC LIBARAY CUSTODIANS LIVED IN THE LIBRARIES
WHEN HE WAS AT THE DINNER TABLE HE THOUGHT HE WAS RICH
HIS FATHER SAID WE ARE NOT RICH, WE'RE POOR
HE FELT ASHAMED AS A CHILD TO LIVE IN A LIBRARY
MOST KIDS WANT TO BE NORMAL AND HE FELT THAT IT WASNT NORMAL
HIS FATHER CLEANED THE LIBRARY VERY WELL
HE WAXED EVERYTHING, THE FLOORS, AND EVEN THE TOPS OF THE BOOKSHELVES
WHEN YOU WENT UP THE STAIRS YOU COULD SEE THE TOP OF THE BOOKSHELVES GLEAMING
DURING THE DAY IN THE LIBRARY, YOU HAD TO BE QUIET
BUT AT NIGHT, YOU COULD RUN AROUND AND HAVE ALL THE FUN YOU WANT
HE LOVED TO READ THE BOOKS IN THE LIBRARY
HE GOT A LOT OF INFORMATION FROM THE BOOKS
EVERYONE ELSE IN HIS FAMILY HADN'T EVEN FINISHED HIGH SCHOOL IN THE PAST
HE WAS THE FIRST TO FINISH HIGH SCHOOL
WHEN HE FINISHED HIGH SCHOOL, HE GOT A JOB AS A PROFESSOR
HE SHOWED HIS DAD THE SIGN ON HIS DOOR THAT SAID PROFESSOR CLARK
HIS DAD LOOKED AT IT, AND JUT GAVE A NOD
BUT HE COULD SEE IT IN HIS EYES THAT HIS FATHER WAS PROUD
THE BOY LIVED WITH HIS MOM AND DAD
HE WOULD STAY UP LATE AND CRAM HIS READING
IN THE SCENE WHERE THEY ARE AT THE DINNER TABLE, HIS OUTFIT CHANGES FROM A SUIT TO A REGULAR OUTFIT
THE STORY TAKES PLACE IN THE 40S
HE DIDN'T REALLY HAVE ANY FRIENDS OVER TO HIS HOUSE
